{"type":"message","id":"8d48a82e","parentId":"de0afa84","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:47:30.485Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_hkxcopc12unu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 044514\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/TIC/experiment_design.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Recent insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - Problem 1 and Problem 2 are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action defined: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define significance scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nBut the immediate next action per the Phase 1 advancement is the TIC Experiment - implementing a classifier on the pulse log files.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist:\r\n- pulse logs in `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n- research documents\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Access the pulse logs\r\n2. Implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Test predictions on next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what logs exist and create the TIC experiment. I'll need to create a script or document that implements this.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pulse log mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 044413.md`\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take is to:\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment script or document that will analyze the pulse logs\r\n2. Implement the classifier logic\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC experiment file that will:\r\n- Read pulse logs\r\n- Classify content as invariant vs variant\r\n- Predict next pulse\r\n- Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nI'll create `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` with the implementation plan and initial code, or better yet, create an actual Python script that can run this analysis.\r\n\r\n\r\nI should prioritize concrete, executable code over documentation. A script that can directly analyze the pulse logs and generate classification results will be more actionable. I'll structure it to handle log parsing, apply the invariance detection algorithm, and output predictions that I can validate against the success criteria.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is solid, but the TIC experiment needs actual implementation code to test the hypothesis. I have pulse logs available and a clear success criteria (70% classification, 60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier to analyze pulse logs, classify invariant vs variant content, and measure prediction accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nTIC_RESULTS = Path(\"research/TIC-RESULTS.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_content(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract meaningful content blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = filepath.read_text()\r\n    # Extract sections: OBSERVATION, ACTION, MUTATION, GOALS updates\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    for match in re.finditer(r'###\\s+(\\w+)\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL):\r\n        sections[match.group(1).strip()] = match.group(2).strip()\r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef tokenize(text):\r\n    \"\"\"Simple tokenization for content comparison.\"\"\"\r\n    return set(re.findall(r'\\b\\w{3,}\\b', text.lower()))\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariants(pulse_contents):\r\n    \"\"\"Find tokens that persist across all pulses = invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n    if not pulse_contents:\r\n        return set(), []\r\n    \r\n    token_sets = [tokenize(c) for c in pulse_contents]\r\n    # Intersection = invariants (present in all)\r\n    invariants = set.intersection(*token_sets) if token_sets else set()\r\n    # Per-pulse unique = variants\r\n    variants = [s - invariants for s in token_sets]\r\n    return invariants, variants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(token_set, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as invariant-rich or variant-rich.\"\"\"\r\n    if not token_set:\r\n        return \"EMPTY\", 0.0\r\n    invariant_overlap = len(token_set & invariants)\r\n    ratio = invariant_overlap / len(token_set) if token_set else 0\r\n    return (\"INVARIANT\" if ratio > 0.3 else \"VARIANT\"), ratio\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_invariants(variants_history, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict which invariants likely appear in next pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    # Simple heuristic: invariants with high frequency across history\r\n    return invariants  # Initial: all invariants persist\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    # Load all pulse logs sorted by timestamp\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=lambda f: f.name)\r\n    print(f\"Found {len(pulse_files)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(\"WARNING: Need at least 5 logs for meaningful experiment\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Extract content from each pulse\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        sections = extract_content(pf)\r\n        content = sections.get('OBSERVATION', '') + ' ' + sections.get('ACTION', '')\r\n        pulses.append({'file': pf.name, 'content': content, 'sections': sections})\r\n    \r\n    # Compute invariants across all pulses\r\n    all_content = [p['content']\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:45:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342050483}}
